name: Rick
line: Don't let any of those things get away, Morty. If their DNA gets into Earth's food chain, our entire species could be sterilized.

name: Morty
line: Then why aren't we killing them?!

name: Rick
line: Great. Next time I need a species sterilized, who's gonna do it for me? You?

name: Morty
line: Oh, Rick! I-Is that the Vindibeacon? We're being called to assemble by the Vindicators!

name: Rick
line: I refuse to answer a literal call to adventure, Morty. Let it go to voicemail!

name: Morty
line: Rick, the Vindicators only call when the universe itself is at stake! They're first line of defense against evil! They're the guardians of the unguarded!

name: Rick
line: They're the writers of their own press releases, Morty! They're a bunch of drama queens that spend an hour talking and twenty minutes jumping around while shit blows up. They're a phase. We did one, it was the big event of that summer. Let it die.

name: Morty
line: I, Morty Smith, invoke my right to choose one in every ten Rick and Morty adventures. [holds up a "Morty Adventure Card" with ten squares and all but one containing a Morty-shaped stamp mark] Read 'em and weep.

name: Rick
line: God... fuckin' dammit! [takes the card] Fine! But don't say I didn't warn you. [stamps the remaining square]

name: Morty
line: [excited] Yes! [presses a button on the Vindibeacon and speaks into it] Vindicator command ship, beacon received! We're doing Vindicators Twoooooooooo!

name: Rick
line: Whoops! Uh, Morty, you might want to freeze some sperm.

name: Supernova
line: [voiceover] Vindicators, Worldender is back...

name: Supernova
line: ..and this time, he's out to end more than worlds. We have reason to believe his stronghold is located on...

name: Rick
line: [interrupting] My balls.

name: Morty
line: Rick!

name: Supernova
line: ...the Terraneus system. Once in range, Million Ants will scan for pheromone activity, which should lead us to the location of the base.

name: Rick
line: Oh, that's Million Ants. I can't see the ants over here. It just assumed that was, uh, Turd Man. Wiggly Turd Man.

name: Morty
line: Rick, stop!

name: Supernova
line: Rick, you have something to add to the briefing?

name: Rick
line: Uh, yeah, just a few more design notes. [points to Crocubot] Um, this guy. The, uh... The, uh...

name: Crocubot
line: I am Crocubot.

name: Rick
line: [laughs] Right, Crocubot. So, you're half-cold, unfeeling reptile, half-also cold, equally-unfeeling machine.

name: Crocubot
line: Yes.

name: Rick
line: So, you're origin is what? Y-You fell into a vat of redundancy?

name: Noob-Noob
line: [sweeping up in the background; snickers] Got damn!

name: Supernova
line: Noob-Noob, we're having a briefing! [to Rick] If I can continue, Rick. I anticipate sophisticated security measures. I trust you can be of service there.

name: Rick
line: Well, let me check my list of powers and weaknesses. Ability to do anything... But only whenever I want... Yeah, that sounds like a job for me.

name: Alan
line: I wish he had the ability to check is attitude.

name: Rick
line: Alan Rails, ladies and gentleman. After his parents' tragic death in a railroad accident, he gained the power to summon ghost trains. It's not all bad, though. They were spared having to see their grown son wear a whistle!

name: Noob-Noob
line: Got damn!

name: Rick
line: Thanks, Noob-Noob! This guy gets it.

name: Morty
line: Vance Maximus, Renegade Star Soldier!

name: Vance
line: Sorry I'm late. It was happy hour.

name: Morty
line: [laughing] Happy hour.

name: Rick
line: Uh, I was also late because of my drinking and mentioned it to zero applause.

name: Vance
line: Rick Sanchez, Tinkerer of Terror. Man, that's hard to say. And... Morty, right?

name: Morty
line: Whoa, yeah!

name: Vance
line: I never forget a kid. [to everyone] What do you say, Vindicators? Let's make this three for three?

name: Morty
line: Did he say "three for three"?

name: Rick
line: Did he say he never forgets a kid?

name: Morty
line: You mean "two for two", right, Vance?

name: Supernova
line: Actually, we assembled a second time last summer to fight Doomnomitron.

name: Morty
line: So, this is... Vindicators 3? And you guys did Vindicators 2... w-without us?

name: Million Ants
line: [beat] I sense... insecurity.

name: Vance
line: Are you sure there's not just a picnic nearby.

name: Rick
line: I guess he found his crowd. Pretty toothless stuff, guys.

name: Rick
line: [spits into the sink and exits the bathroom] I hope you're happy with the adventure so far, Morty. These guys are even lamer than last time.

name: Morty
line: We weren't here "last time", remember? They did a whole Vindicators without us. A bunch of them got killed, too. They lost Lady Katana, Calypso, Diablo Verde...

name: Rick
line: Yikes. Yeah, things did feel less diverse in there. [goes back into the bathroom and continues brushing]

name: Morty
line: This article says the reason we weren't involved was... "personality conflicts".

name: Rick
line: Don't worry, Morty, they love you. Superheroes need a wide-eyed unremarkable to tag along and react to everything like it's mind-blowing.

name: Morty
line: I... think the personality conflict might have been... you.

name: Rick
line: [spits] Jesus... How awesome is that? I mean, they wanted to not need me so bad, they murdered three innocent heroes of color, and they still had to bring me back?

name: Morty
line: Rick, since it's my adventure and all, could you do me a favor?

name: Rick
line: Uh, the adventure is the favor, Morty. Me sleeping on these linens is the favor. I mean, w-w-w-what--what are we vindicating? Comfort?

name: Morty
line: Rick, this really bums me out. It-It's embarrassing to find out these guys don't like us.

name: Rick
line: Why? Morty, [burp] I defeat gagoos more powerful than these guys every week.

name: Morty
line: Yeah, but not heroes.

name: Rick
line: Oh, please. They just call themselves heroes so they can...

name: Morty
line: I'm calling them that, Rick! They're my heroes! Mine! [angrily lies down in his bed]

name: Rick
line: Huh... no accounting for taste. I'm gonna go get a drink.

name: PA System
line: Good morning, Vindicators. Ship has arrived at Terraneus system. All Vindicators report to the... briefing room. The--The room from the, uh... the... Uh, it's the d--It's a different room than--than... conference room. I'm sorry, it's my first day as a PA system. First day jitters. [imitates radio crackle]

name: Morty
line: [mortified] Oh, God.

name: Supernova
line: Good morning. Looks like your grandpa had a long night. Crocubot, why don't you escort Mr. Sanchez to a more comfortable spot so that someone can... [sigh] clean up his diarrhea.

name: Noob-Noob
line: Whoa, I'm nervous about my first mission.

name: Supernova
line: Actually, Noob-Noob, you have a new mission. [makes the guns and ammo disappear and conjures a mop]

name: Noob-Noob
line: [sadly] Got... damn.

name: Supernova
line: Vindicators, prepare for arrival.

name: Vance
line: Morty, the Vindicators and I had a chat this morning and I'm afraid we need to make a little change.

name: Morty
line: [sigh] I-I totally get it. I-I'm so sorry.

name: Vance
line: You should be. [opens a locker, takes out a blue Vindicator vest and tosses it to Morty] Running around in a yellow t-shirt like you're not one of us? Disgraceful.

name: Morty
line: [tongue-tied] I-I-I... I'm not a superhero.

name: Vance
line: Cop a squat, chief. [they sit down] Everyone in the universe is a hero. All you have to do is know the difference between good and bad, and root for good.

name: Morty
line: Rick says "good" and "bad" are artificial constructs.

name: Vance
line: Yeah, well, I get the feeling... he kind of needs that to be the case. [to Noob-Noob] Not coming, Noob-Noob?

name: Noob-Noob
line: [slips on some diarrhea] Ohh! No, uh, I... I got stuff to do here.

name: Vance
line: Security drones, inbound.

name: Supernova
line: Star Mother, grant me your wrath! [echoes]

name: Alan
line: All aboard!

name: Million Ants
line: Aah! [goes back and faces the team] Gun turret.

name: Supernova
line: Are you all right?

name: Million Ants
line: Yes. I only lost 400 ants. My queen is laying more. [his holes are now gone] I am back to one million ants.

name: Supernova
line: Someone wake up Sanchez.

name: Rick
line: Ugh! Oh, Christ...

name: Supernova
line: Rick, you're up.

name: Rick
line: Barely.

name: Supernova
line: Rick, we're taking fire from an automated turret. Can you bring it offline?

name: Rick
line: Uh-huh.

name: Rick
line: Uh, my God, that's better.

name: Supernova
line: RICK!

name: Rick
line: Hey, I can't help if I can't see.

name: Alan
line: I could've just used a ghost train.

name: Rick
line: Really? You don't say. You would have used a ghost train? [sarcastic] Hey, everybody, the ghost train guy would have used a ghost train!

name: Alan
line: Man, fuck you.

name: Rick
line: Is there coffee? Hey, Morty, can you be a pal? Grandpa left his coffee maker on the ship. Y-You know, the French press thing?

name: Morty
line: [annoyed] Get it yourself.

name: Rick
line: Little extra [burp] snippy this morning, aren't you?

name: Morty
line: Just focus on the mission, all right?

name: Rick
line: [sarcastic] Oh, oh, oh, I'm sorry. Oh, you're right. Ooh, real serious. Gotta take it real serious, huh? [makes a gun sign with his hand and moves forward]

name: Alan
line: [gasp] Son of a steam engine! They're all dead!

name: Crocubot
line: Why would Worldender do this to his own men... and several women?

name: Vance
line: Well, he is the Worldender. The guy ends worlds. Kind of his thing.

name: Rick
line: [still sarcastic] Ooh, real scared. Real fucking on alert, high alert over here.

name: Vance
line: What the FUCK?!

name: Supernova
line: It's Worldender! What happened to him?

name: Worldender
line: [weak, pain-filled moan]

name: Million Ants
line: I sense his life force is fading.

name: Rick
line: Million Ants, ladies and gentleman! The ant colony with the power of two human eyes!

name: Rick
line: All right. Short mission, good mission. Remember when Alan wanted to use a ghost train? See you guys in Vindicators 4. Morty?

name: Morty
line: Rick, whoever did this is an even bigger threat than Worldender! We can't leave now!

name: Supernova
line: He's right. This is far from over.

name: Rick
line: Well, have fun with that. But Morty and I have to meet a comet girl, a monorail man, two assholes and a full alligator in, like, an hour.

name: Rick
line: Shit.

name: Million Ants
line: I sense the presence of a greater evil.

name: Drunk Rick
line: Check, check, One, two. Okay, is it recording? Good. Hello, Vindicators. Welcome to your reckoning, babyyyyyyyy!!

name: Rick
line: Welp, it's official. I had too much to drink last night.

name: Drunk Rick
line: [adjusts camera] If you guys are watching this, you're, you know, the Vindicators. So now that we know...

name: Vance
line: [points his arm cannons at Rick] Rick? What's going on, buddy?

name: Rick
line: Obviously, I came here last night during a blackout.

name: Supernova
line: Obviously? You came here and defeated our arch-nemesis while so drunk, you don't remember doing it? That's something obvious to you?

name: Rick
line: Look, I'm a lit--[burp] little more complex than you guys and, no offense, but I've always suspected that a lot of what you do in a year could be knocked out in a couple of hours.

name: Drunk Rick
line: ...So I thought, why not just do your job for you so we can have a little fun game. [points to the left]

name: Morty
line: Rick, is-is this a "Saw" thing? Are you seriously "Saw"-ing the Vindicators?

name: Rick
line: Morty I'm a drunk, not a hack.

name: Drunk Rick
line: If you break the rules, lose the game or try to leave, you will die. Like in [burp] "Sawwww".

name: Rick
line: [embarrassed] Well, I-I-I think we've seen enough. I'll just figure out how to unplug this. [runs somewhere]

name: Drunk Rick
line: Okay, here we go, room number one. The Vindicators are known throughout the galaxy, but do they know yourselves? Do you know yourselves? Match your... your shit, your... your gimmicks with your faces and y-you get it, it's a matching thing. And do it in three minutes, or you'll [burp] all die.

name: Vance
line: Screw this. I'm not playing his game. I'm gonna find us a way out of here.

name: Rick
line: Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hold on, Vance. He said you'd die if you tried to leave. That means there's booby traps.

name: Vance
line: Why are you acting like that's not you?!

name: Rick
line: What part of "blackout" don't you understand? I thought you drank?

name: Vance
line: Like cool drinking! Like sexy drinking, not this psycho trailer-park shit!

name: Morty
line: Vance, stay calm...

name: Vance
line: Oh, so you're the leader now because we gave you a jacket?! You're the learning-disabled kid we do photo-ops with!

name: Morty
line: Okay, ouch, but...

name: Vance
line: [hyperventilating] Okay, this... this is triggering me. I need space. I-I need SPACE! FROM THIS!

name: Alan
line: Give me one good reason why I shouldn't crush your windpipe!

name: Rick
line: Because my epidermis is laced with a nanofiber defense mesh.

name: Rick
line: And because, like I said, I don't remember last night.

name: Alan
line: I told you not to invite this mummified motherfucker back!

name: Rick
line: Alan, I'm not proud of what's happening here, but if you keep coming at me, there's gonna be another passenger on that ghost train.

name: Morty
line: Guys! [finishes placing the cards underneath the pictures] I've figured it out.

name: Drunk Rick
line: Congrats! You did it--[burp] it!

name: Morty
line: It was a bit. All of the descriptors apply to all of you. Drunk Rick's point is that none of you are very special or different. [despondent] That's always his point.

name: Supernova
line: Let's just get through this as quickly as possible. Then, we'll deal with the two of you.

name: Morty
line: The two of us?! [to Rick] I hope you're proud of yourself!

name: Rick
line: Uh, I kind of am. I saved the goddamn universe.

name: Morty
line: That's not the issue, Rick!

name: Rick
line: Ahh, it would've been if I hadn't.

name: Drunk Rick
line: The Vindicators say their job is... is to fight evil wherever it hides, but they don't... pick the location you'll... you'll never even hear them mention, because to fight darkness is to fight yourself.

name: Crocubot
line: Oh, I know this! Dorian 5! [walks toward the hologram]

name: Supernova
line: Crocubot, don't!

name: Crocubot
line: [swiping through the map] There's no other possible answer. My mechanical and reptilian logic are certain of it.

name: Rick
line: Huh, I'm seeing more croc than bot here.

name: Supernova
line: Goddammit!

name: Morty
line: Uh, what happened on Dorian 5?

name: Supernova
line: Nothing!

name: Alan
line: Nothing?! We exterminated a planet!

name: Morty
line: W-Wait, huh?

name: Supernova
line: Doomnomitron was hiding here! He's a shapeshifter! Destroying Dorian 5 was the only way to kill him!

name: Drunk Rick
line: Come on, guys, we're all thinking it. Don't... [cough] Don't make me say it.

name: Morty
line: [with annoyed realization] Oh, o-okay. This again? [talks toward the hologram]

name: Rick
line: You know, [burp] I could have made a device to detect Doomnomitron from orbit like [snap] that.

name: Supernova
line: I'm not the one that didn't want you back. Alan was!

name: Alan
line: [threateningly] If you lay those deaths at my doorstep one more time...

name: Million Ants
line: [appears between them] Do not threaten her!

name: Drunk Rick
line: Congrats, you did it!

name: Supernova
line: What the hell is Is-ra-el?

name: Morty
line: I-It's just something Rick starts talking about whenever he's blackout drunk.

name: Rick
line: W-What? In w--In w-w-what--In what way? Like, w-w-what's my point?

name: Morty
line: In a way that has no point! You just babble about defense budgets and the United Nations, and then you pass out!

name: Rick
line: So, to be clear, I sometimes reference the geopolitical complexities of the topic, which is not the same as going to an anti-Semitic place.

name: Million Ants
line: I have no stake in this.

name: Rick
line: I don't either. I-I'm just saying, if anything, the drunk version of me is probably so supportive of Israel, he wants what's best for it and...

name: Million Ants
line: Hey, man, I'm not touching this. You do you.

name: Drunk Rick
line: Aloha... means hello and goodbye in Hawaii. But, uh, aloha means... has nothing to do with this room. [cough] I'm so fucking drunk. Ugh, okay, here's the deal. I-I want to rest my eyes for a little bit. I'm--I'm not going to sleep. I just... just need to rest my eye, so let's make this one simple. Just try to hit some three-pointers.

name: Drunk Rick
line: let's say... you have to hit... five three-pointers in... five minutes or, I don't know, the whole place--the whole planet will get blown up with a n-neutrino bomb. And try to make it a-a lesson about yourselves like, like how... selfish you a-are, or something. Also, Hawaii.

name: Morty
line: [sigh] You guys hit the baskets. I'll disarm the drunkenly-improvised neutrino bomb. There's a 40% chance it's a dud, but y-you should still stay back. [starts working on the bomb]

name: Rick
line: Morty, how many of these...?

name: Morty
line: [angrily] Too many, Rick! Too many!

name: Rick
line: Man, I am really getting high-roaded today. [walks to join Morty]

name: Drunk Rick
line: That's a three-pointer!

name: Alan
line: Nice shot.

name: Million Ants
line: Thank you.

name: Alan
line: You two make quite a team. [tosses the ball to Million Ants]

name: Supernova
line: We all do.

name: Alan
line: Yeah, I guess.

name: Drunk Rick
line: That's a three-pointer!

name: Alan
line: [sounding jealous] But you guys have always had a... an unspoken bond.

name: Alan
line: I mean, really unspoken. Like, "let's-not-tell-my-husband" unspoken.

name: Supernova
line: [annoyed] We aren't married anymore, Alan.

name: Alan
line: [becoming aggressive] Sure, but were we married when you two were "stranded" on Delphi 6 for three days? Because I sensed something was weird when you can back. But what do I know about sensitivity? I'm just a phantom train conductor. You're the pile of ordinary bugs that fucked my wife!

name: Drunk Rick
line: That's a three-pointer!

name: Rick
line: Where the fuck is the lead wire?!

name: Morty
line: You always put it in the weirdest place! Um, uh, over here, maybe?

name: Rick
line: Jesus Christ, what a shitty neutrino bomb. It's a miracle I actually every destroy anything.

name: Morty
line: Oh, I don't know. You managed to destroy just about everything today; the villains, the heroes, the lines between them, my childhood...

name: Rick
line: Thank you. I appreciate it, Morty. I know you were sucking the Kool-Aid out of the Vindicators' dicks, so the fact that I was right about them must be pretty hard to admit.

name: Morty
line: Yeah, it is. You know why, Rick? Because when you're an asshole, it doesn't matter how right you are, nobody wants to give you the satisfaction.

name: Rick
line: I know. Everyone wants people they like to be right. That's why popular people are fucking dumb. And why your pretentious, poorly-written, high-budget friends back there can eat a double-decker shit sandwich. [the bomb powers down] Disarmed.

name: Morty
line: [with realization] Holy shit. You're jealous.

name: Supernova
line: YES! Is that what you want to hear?!

name: Alan
line: Did it feel good?! Did you like his six million wriggling legs more than my tragedy-stricken, half-ghost, half-tumescent penis?!

name: Drunk Rick
line: That's a three-pointer!

name: Morty
line: Guys, stop! You're just proving my asshole grandpa right!

name: Supernova
line: [growing sad] You wish this was about sex! We loved each other! We had a child together.

name: Alan
line: WHAT?!

name: Supernova
line: [crying] I conceived a child with Million Ants and it died inside me because it as HALF A MILLION ANTS AND HALF COLLAPSING STAR! And yes, he was better than you!

name: Alan
line: Yeah?

name: Million Ants
line: [morphs into a larger attack form] One million times better!

name: Alan
line: ALL ABOOOOOOARD, MOTHERFUCKER!!!

name: Supernova
line: STOP! [echoes]

name: Rick
line: Oof! Didn't see that comin'.

name: Supernova
line: Is that sarcasm?! [conjures handcuffs onto Rick and Morty] I don't want you slipping away then this is over! All of these deaths are on your hands!

name: Rick
line: Oh, come on, maybe a couple of them, but definitely not the train guy.

name: Supernova
line: All of them.

name: Rick
line: O-kayyy...

name: Drunk Rick
line: Congrats, you did it!

name: Drunk Rick
line: All right, by now, I've been pretty clear that I think the Vindicators are [cough] full of shit. But... you do have one thing I'll never have. And that thing is the only part of the Vindicators with any value to me. If you know what it is, place it on the platform.  Guess wrong and the pla... planet will explode. And probably the solar system, 'cause I kind of fucking eyeballed the neutrino bombs on this one.

name: Supernova
line: So what's the trick? Morty, you're the Drunk Rick expert.

name: Morty
line: I think... no matter what we put on there, we die. He said it's the part of the Vindicators he values. That means nothing. He wants our last moment alive to be spent knowing how few fucks he gave.

name: Supernova
line: Jesus! Okay, open to second opinions!

name: Rick
line: I could--It could be Morty.

name: Morty
line: What?

name: Rick
line: Hey, I don't know. I mean, look, when I get drunk, I get stupid and emotional and there's no logic to it. It's, like, possible I got so drunk, I felt like I was losing Morty to the Vindicators, and maybe this is my way of saying "Okay, you can have him, but only if you know how important he is, otherwise I'll kill you."

name: Million Ants
line: That is a... really specific guess.

name: Rick
line: Look, I... there's nothing in the room but us. I'm just using logic to connect some dots. It's the best guess I've got.

name: Supernova
line: But you're betting our lives on it.

name: Morty
line: [smiling smugly, starting walking toward the platform] I'll cover that bet. I get it.

name: Rick
line: Well, Morty, I think you're making that smirky face because you're misinterpreting the moment. I am not being coy about some hidden love for you. I want to be really clear that, if anyone has a better guess, like, if I gave you an amulet last night, or...

name: Rick
line: Oh, shit.

name: Drunk Rick
line: Sorry, I'm... not good at goodbyes. It looks like I'm never gonna see you again. I can't really roll with the hero types, and I don't... th-they don't want me around. But I want... you to know, even if I didn't show it at the time, II really appreciated you sticking by me.

name: Drunk Rick
line: [getting emotional] Goddammit, why am I crying? It makes no sense.

name: Morty
line: [he is touched and wipes tears from his eyes]

name: Drunk Rick
line: Ugh, y-you're probably confused because we barely know each other...

name: Morty
line: [his expression becomes puzzled]

name: Drunk Rick
line: ...but you really stuck your neck out [burp] when you gave me props for my awesome jokes in the briefing room. Everybody else had their heads so far up their ass. Even my own grandson is like, "Oh, the Vindicators are so cool." I mean, he's a moron, it's their... demographic. But you're different, Noob-Noob.

name: Morty
line: [getting angry] ...Motherfucker!

name: Drunk Rick
line: [crying] You're fucking cool! And you're smart! And I bet we coulda hung out and shit! And I hope you get to be a full-fledged Vindicator! A-And d-do me a favor. Do-Don't let him know I... I got emotional. But you can tell him one thing. Tell him I said... Oh, fuck. Okay, I just shit myself. Okay, later.

name: Rick
line: W--Dude, Morty, what happened i...?

name: Morty
line: Shut up.

name: Million Ants
line: I sense this means we are not dying.

name: Supernova
line: Not all of us.

name: Million Ants
line: Sweetheart?

name: Supernova
line: Just let Titty-Bean do this, Snuzzles. It's for the greater good.

name: Morty
line: [gagging] Greater good?!

name: Rick
line: [also gagging] Titty-Bean?

name: Supernova
line: It's like you said, Morty

name: Morty
line: Never said that!

name: Supernova
line: It's the galaxy's faith in the Vindicators that keeps the galaxy secure!

name: Rick
line: [sarcastic] Yeah, I feel safer already.

name: Morty
line: No doubt. Who do we make the check out to?

name: Rick
line: I'll say, we are gettin' some good licks in while choking to death.

name: Morty
line: Right?

name: Million Ants
line: Titty-Bean, listen to me. When you came to me, I was merely a sentient colony of ants. It was your beliefs, your pursuit of justice, that taught me to be a man.

name: Supernova
line: When did it get so complicated?

name: Million Ants
line: Who knows? But we can make it simple again.

name: Supernova
line: You were always the romantic. [sinister] Which is why you can't leave either.

name: Supernova
line: Goodbye, my love.

name: Rick
line: Damn! She double-crossed Snuzzles!

name: Supernova
line: Silence! I'm going to enjoy this...

name: Announcer
line: Let's give a huge thanks to Rick Sanchez for killing Worldender, putting this awesome party together, and for booking one of the hottest talents out there

name: Logic
line: [offscreen] Aww, yeah! [starts rapping]

name: Rick
